      "content": "it's just that i've read online that melatonin is basically just a hormone and it shouldn't interfere much with the actual drug, it just kind of prepares the body. if i just take a small dose of melatonin with the zolpidem, isn't that basically just helping the prescription work more effectively? it seems like a common sense way to get better results when the prescription alone isn't cutting it.",
